{"id":"mai-4z3y","kind":"ticket","type":"epic","title":"Delphi: CRDT doc sync breaks under Obsidian editing","tags":["research","delphi"],"body":"Parallel oracle investigation of how to fix the CRDT-based document sync in maitake so it works correctly with Obsidian.\n\n## Symptom\nWhen editing docs in Obsidian, the CRDT merge produces massively duplicated content — same line fragments repeated 40+ times. The document becomes garbled and unusable.\n\n## Known Code Locations\n- pkg/crdt/crdt.go — CRDT TextDoc backed by y-crdt/yrs WASM\n- pkg/crdt/diff.go — Myers diff to compute insert/delete ops\n- pkg/notes/docs.go — SyncDocs bidirectional sync, mergeViaCRDT function\n- cmd/mai/daemon.go — fsnotify watcher, debounce, syncFile\n\n## Observable Facts\n- mergeViaCRDT uses creationBody as the 3-way merge base (the original note body from creation time)\n- lastSyncBody() has a TODO and returns empty string\n- The daemon runs full SyncDocs on every debounced file change\n- Obsidian saves frequently (on every keystroke or focus change)\n- The CRDT peers start from the same base but both apply large diffs from an ancient base to current content\n- This causes the CRDT to see both sides as having independently inserted identical content — keeping both copies","timestamp":"2026-04-03T12:01:50Z","branch":"main"}
